The paper deals with a network of unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs) and their communication with a ground user equipment (UE). This falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also considers the interference received at the reference UE, which involves information theory (cs.IT). The proposed 3D mobility model is a combination of random waypoint mobility and uniform mobility, which falls under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper also evaluates the coverage probability under Nakagami-m fading, which involves system modeling and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper quantifies the achievable performance gains, which involves game theory (cs.GT).
